@plannerLLM text
Use plannerLLM only to propose or repair SOP Lang programs under the control of the native planning command.
Its output should be raw SOP Lang that names concrete intermediate families, uses only available command or interpreter names, makes dependencies explicit through $family references, and converges into one final @response declaration without dead-end families.
Prefer it when the runtime needs decomposition, rerouting, plan normalization, or repair after a failed declaration.
Avoid using plannerLLM as an ordinary answer writer, a hidden reasoning sink, or a place to smuggle prose into native commands.
